### CurrencyLibrary
#### Designed by Mikolaj Budzinski

Applications use the following technologies: SpringBoot , Java.

To run the application, you need to open a Linux teminal(Intelij terminal).

---Type the command:
.mvnw clean install

---The next command is:
.\mvnw spring-boot:run

---After this action, open the page:
http://localhost:8080   

---Now you can choose which of the commands you want to execute:
*/currency-library/average/{sign}/{localDate}
*/currency-library/minMax/{sign}/{counting}/{localDate}
*/currency-library/buyAsk/{sign}/{localDate}

---In this code, we substitute currency abbreviations under the {sign} character

---In this code under the {counting} character we substitute the number of dates we want to check as provided by the task command

---In this code we substitute under the {localDate} character as a date stamp in the form YYYY-MM-DD

###Examples
--First example:
http://localhost:8080/currency-library/average/USD/2023-04-21

--Second example:
http://localhost:8080/currency-library/minMax/EUR/100/2023-04-24

--Third example:
http://localhost:8080/currency-library/buyAsk/USD/2023-04-25

###Thank you for attention










